claim.claim-text:
1. A device for eliminating one or more trimmings from a series of articles fed to said device, comprising: 
at least one continuous flexible suction conveyor which is equipped with openings and which conveys said articles along a transfer path from a feeder to a receiver, a discharge point for the trimmings being provided along the transfer path; 
and a suction system which is associated with said conveyor and which generates a suction through said openings along said transfer path; characterized by at least one obturator element which is movable along said transfer path and which temporarily closes said openings of the conveyor opposite said at least one trimming, the obturator being operated independently from the conveyor.

14. A method for eliminating one or more trimmings from series of articles fed to a device, in which the articles are engaged by means of suction by a continuous flexible suction conveyor and transported along a transfer path, characterized by: 
inserting into said transfer path at least one obturator element which is separated from said conveyor and which enters between said conveyor and said trimming or trimmings; 
and moving said obturator element together with the conveyor along the transfer path in order to intercept the suction opposite said trimming or trimmings, causing the elimination of the trimming or trimmings from said transfer path as a result of falling.
